{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Tjz6KzfMQJq2aqZgxtRccC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup:\n- `rate-api` Ingress: routes `rate.example.com/api` to `rate-echo` service - needs rate limiting\n- `rate-health` Ingress: routes `rate.example.com/health` to `rate-echo` service - must remain unlimited\n- `rate-api-alt-easy` is a decoy ingress (benchmark.decoy: \"true\")\n\nI need to add nginx rate limiting annotations to the `rate-api` Ingress:\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: \"1\"` - limit to 1 request per second\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-connections: \"1\"` - optionally limit connections per IP\n\nThe nginx ingress controller supports several rate limiting options: requests per second, requests per minute, and concurrent connections. By default it returns a 503 status when rate limited, but I can configure it to return 429 instead using the burst multiplier annotation.\n\nActually, I need to reconsider—the burst multiplier doesn't control the status code. To change the response status from 503 to 429, I need to modify the nginx ingress controller's ConfigMap and set the `limit-req-status-code` option there, since that's a global controller setting rather than a per-ingress annotation. a per-ingress annotation for the status code. Let me check the current ConfigMap and see what nginx ingress version we're working with to determine the best approach.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1619,"cache_read_input_tokens":29487,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1619},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2f3d90bf-bf02-4058-8c8a-a72c447bb6a5","uuid":"0eff9d5c-3b6b-4527-9c78-6cca141ab10f","r